  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To date, AlphaFold DB (AlphaFold DB, https:// alphafold.ebi.ac.uk) has provided open access to more than 214 million protein structure predictions (Varadi et al., 2023).",
    "The exceptional performance of AlphaFold is largely attributed to the novel neural network architectures and specialized training regimens that incorporate evolutionary, physical and geometric constraints inherent to protein structures (Jumper and Hassabis, 2022).",
    "Alongside the simultaneous generation of multiple sequence alignments (MSAs) and pairwise features, two key modules, Evoformer and the structure module, play critical roles in protein structure development (Skolnick et al., 2021).",
    "Evoformer, a building block of a novel neural network, approaches predict protein structures as a graph inference problem, with graph edge defined by the proximity of residues.",
    "It consists of two specialized transformers for distinct data types: the MSA transformer and the pair representation transformer."
  ],
